properties.Title: MIAMI, FL - CRITICAL MASS CROWD-YANGING
properties.Description:
From the Miami Bike Scene website:
“Critical Mass is a cycling event typically held on the last Friday of every month; its purpose is not usually formalized beyond the direct action of meeting at a set location and time and traveling as a group through city or town streets on bicycles.”

For November there were HUNDREDS of cyclists in attendance. These are all mostly local people, of all demographics. They all gather at the starting point on their bike at the start of the event, and just hang out until it begins. That’s where we’ll be operating. We’ll be handing out business cards and engaging in conversations if anyone is open to it.

The official time for gathering at the starting line is 6:30, the biking starts at 7:15. I wanted to get started at 6:15 to catch the early birds as well. That’s only about an hour to Yang hundreds of riders. The more of us there, and the earlier we start, the more people we can get to :)

I will be at the starting line (coordinates below) wearing a neon pink cap to provide everyone with cards to hand out. Should be hard to miss, but I’ll be checking my messages just in case. Make sure to wear your Yang merch!!!

If you would like to participate in the event after the Yanging, feel free to do so. Guidelines are on the Miami Bike Scene website:
https://www.themiamibikescene.com/p/miami-critical-mass-guidelines.html

Starting line/Meeting spot coordinates:

25.7750256,-80.1968508

Hourly Parking near intersection of NW 2nd St and NW 1st Ave:

25.7760478,-80.194815

Where I parked last time (only $5 for whole night):

25.7760576,-80.1942459

For carpooling options email me! I can seat 3-4 more people in my car.

properties.Title: Council Bluffs, IA - Fremont County Field Trip
properties.Description:
Guess what? There are only NINE MORE WEEKENDS until the caucus!

Help us make this weekend count by canvassing in Fremont County. Fremont County is in the southwestern corner of the state. In 2016, only 117 democrats caucused. That means we only need 20 people in the county in order to be viable. If you want to help us convince 20 people to show up and fight for Andrew Yang, join us on Saturday and/or Sunday!

We will be carpooling from Council Bluffs. On Saturday, we'll meet at the CB Office at 10:00 am and be back by 7:00 pm. On Sunday, we'll meet at the CB Office at 11:00 am and be back by 8:00 pm. After we canvass on Sunday, we'll stop by the Fremont County Democrats Social and talk to the county party chairs about why Andrew is the best option for Iowa.

If you can only participate in part of the day, you will have to arrange your own transportation. Please let me know if you have any questions!
